use aiken/collection/list

fn prefix_with_index(items: List<ByteArray>) -> List<ByteArray> {
  list.indexed_foldr(
    items,
    [],
    fn(i, item, acc) {
      let prefix = when i is {
        0 -> "0:"
        1 -> "1:"
        2 -> "2:"
        _ -> "?:"
      }
      [bytearray.concat(prefix, item), ..acc]
    },
  )
}
```

> **Note:** Aiken does not have a built-in integer-to-string conversion in stdlib, so the example above uses a `when` pattern for small known indices. For a production use-case you would need a custom int-to-bytearray helper. The `indexed_foldr` call itself is idiomatic: the callback receives `(i, item, acc)` and prepends the prefixed element to the accumulator.

