  list.indexed_foldr(
    items,
    [],
    fn(i, x, acc) {
      if i % 2 == 0 {
        [x, ..acc]
      } else {
        acc
      }
    },
  )
}
```

Because `indexed_foldr` traverses right-to-left but provides the original 0-based indices, prepending even-indexed elements to the accumulator yields them in the correct ascending order.

