    let ventana = interval.entirely_between(2000, 8000)
    // Verifica que el rango de validez de la tx esté completamente dentro de la ventana
    interval.includes(ventana, self.validity_range)
  }
}
```

`interval.entirely_between(2000, 8000)` produce un intervalo con `is_inclusive: False` en ambos extremos, lo que significa que el slot 2000 y el 8000 quedan **excluidos**. La función `interval.includes` comprueba que `self.validity_range` esté completamente dentro de ese intervalo.

According to the Aiken documentation, `interval.entirely_between(10, 100)` produces the following `Interval` value:

```aiken
Interval {
  lower_bound: IntervalBound {
    bound_type: Finite(10),
    is_inclusive: False,
  },
  upper_bound: IntervalBound {
    bound_type: Finite(100),
    is_inclusive: False,
  },
}
```

Both bounds are **finite** and **non-inclusive**, making this a strictly open interval — neither `10` nor `100` are part of the interval. This corresponds to the mathematical notation $(10, 100)$.

You can verify membership with `interval.contains`:
```aiken
