- `address.from_script(target_script_hash)` derives the script address (no delegation rights).
- `list.any` checks that at least one output both targets the script address and carries a positive quantity of the minted policy.

`cardano/address.from_verification_key` takes a `Hash<Blake2b_224, VerificationKey>` (a 28-byte verification key hash) and returns an `Address` with no delegation rights. Example usage:

```aiken
use cardano/address
use aiken/crypto.{VerificationKeyHash}

fn get_address(vkh: VerificationKeyHash) -> address.Address {
  address.from_verification_key(vkh)
}
```

The resulting address has its payment credential set to the provided verification key hash and has no staking/delegation credential attached.

```aiken
use aiken/collection/list
use aiken/crypto.{VerificationKeyHash}
use cardano/address
use cardano/transaction.{OutputReference, Transaction}

pub type Datum {
  owner: VerificationKeyHash,
}

validator owner_lock {
  spend(
    datum: Option<Datum>,
    _redeemer: Void,
    _own_ref: OutputReference,
    self: Transaction,
  ) -> Bool {
    when datum is {
      Some(d) -> list.has(self.extra_signatories, d.owner)
      None -> False
    }
  }
}
```

```aiken
use aiken/collection/list
use aiken/crypto.{VerificationKeyHash}
use cardano/address
use cardano/assets.{PolicyId}
use cardano/transaction.{Output, Transaction}

pub type MintRedeemer {
  beneficiary: VerificationKeyHash,
