`Spend(OutputReference)` is one of the variants of `ScriptPurpose` in `cardano/transaction`. It is used for scripts that act as **payment credentials** for addresses in transaction outputs — they govern the rules by which the output they reference can be spent.

When a transaction tries to spend a UTxO locked at a script address, the validator associated with that address is invoked with the `Spend(OutputReference)` purpose, where the `OutputReference` identifies the specific UTxO being consumed.

In Aiken v3, this maps directly to the `spend` handler:

```aiken
use cardano/transaction.{OutputReference, Transaction}

validator my_spend_validator {
  spend(datum: Option<MyDatum>, redeemer: MyRedeemer, own_ref: OutputReference, self: Transaction) -> Bool {
    // own_ref is the OutputReference of the UTxO being spent
    // self is the full transaction context
    True
  }
}
```

The `own_ref: OutputReference` parameter directly corresponds to the `Spend(OutputReference)` script purpose variant.

```aiken
use aiken/collection/list
use aiken/crypto.{VerificationKeyHash}
use cardano/transaction.{OutputReference, Transaction}

pub type SpendDatum {
  owner: VerificationKeyHash,
}

validator require_signer {
  spend(
    datum: Option<SpendDatum>,
    _redeemer: Void,
    _own_ref: OutputReference,
    self: Transaction,
  ) -> Bool {
    when datum is {
      Some(d) -> list.has(self.extra_signatories, d.owner)
      None -> False
    }
  }
}
```

The validator unwraps the `Option<SpendDatum>` datum, then verifies that `d.owner` is present in `self.extra_signatories` using `list.has/2`.

Dentro de un validador `spend` en Aiken v3, el parámetro `own_ref: OutputReference` identifica el UTxO que se está gastando. Puedes usar `transaction.find_input` para resolver ese `OutputReference` a su `Input` completo (que incluye el valor y la dirección):

```aiken
use cardano/transaction.{OutputReference, Transaction, find_input}

validator inspect_input {
  spend(
    _datum: Option<Void>,
    _redeemer: Void,
    own_ref: OutputReference,
    self: Transaction,
  ) -> Bool {
    when find_input(self.inputs, own_ref) is {
      Some(input) -> {
        // input.output.value contiene el valor del UTxO
        // input.output_reference == own_ref
        True
      }
      None -> False
    }
  }
}
```

`find_input` recibe la lista `self.inputs` y el `own_ref`, y retorna `Option<Input>`. Si no encuentra la entrada (lo que no debería ocurrir en un gasto válido), el validador falla retornando `False`.

```aiken
use aiken/interval
use cardano/transaction.{OutputReference, Transaction}

pub type TimeLockDatum {
  deadline: Int,
}

validator time_lock {
  spend(
    datum: Option<TimeLockDatum>,
    _redeemer: Void,
    _own_ref: OutputReference,
    self: Transaction,
  ) -> Bool {
    when datum is {
      Some(d) ->
        interval.is_entirely_after(self.validity_range, d.deadline)
      None -> False
    }
  }
}
```

`interval.is_entirely_after(self.validity_range, d.deadline)` returns `True` only when the entire validity range of the transaction falls strictly after the deadline, ensuring the spend cannot occur before the lock expires.

