    redeemer == MintToken
  }
}
```

The `redeemer: MintAction` parameter is automatically decoded from the underlying `Redeemer = Data`. The validator returns `True` only when the decoded value is `MintToken`, rejecting any transaction that supplies a `BurnToken` redeemer.

En Aiken, `self.redeemers` es de tipo `Pairs<ScriptPurpose, Redeemer>` donde `Redeemer = Data`. Puedes usar `list.all` para recorrer los pares y rechazar cualquiera cuyo valor sea el redeemer no deseado.

```aiken
use aiken/collection/list
use cardano/transaction.{Transaction, OutputReference, ScriptPurpose, Redeemer}

