output:
The manual approach above is incomplete — it ignores the datum hash entirely and also misses witness-set datums. Replace it with `transaction.find_datum`, which correctly checks the witness set first and then inline datums:

```aiken
use cardano/transaction.{Transaction, OutputReference, find_datum}

validator refactored_validator {
  spend(
    datum: Option<ByteArray>,
    redeemer: Void,
    own_ref: OutputReference,
    self: Transaction,
  ) -> Bool {
    when datum is {
      None -> False
      Some(target_hash) ->
        // Idiomatic: find_datum checks witness set first, then inline datums
        when find_datum(self.outputs, self.datums, target_hash) is {
          None -> False
          Some(_data) -> True
        }
    }
  }
}
```

**What changed and why:**
- Removed the manual `list.find_map` loop — it was neither hash-checking nor witness-aware.
- `find_datum(self.outputs, self.datums, target_hash)` encapsulates both lookup strategies in one call.
- The `datums` field (`self.datums`) provides the witness-set dict, which the manual approach completely ignored.

